\v 9 \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G3004"\w* \w told|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w parable|strong="G3850"\w* \add to illustrate what God would do to the Jews who rejected the former prophets and himself\add*: “\w A|strong="G2532"\w* \add certain\add* \w man|strong="G3778"\w* \w planted|strong="G5452"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* vineyard. \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w rented|strong="G1554"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* vineyard \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w some|strong="G3588"\w* \w men|strong="G3778"\w* \add to care for it and to give him some of the grapes in return\add*. \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* country \w and|strong="G2532"\w* stayed \w there|strong="G2532"\w* several years.
