\v 19 \w The|strong="G1722"\w* \w chief|strong="G2532"\w* priests \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w men|strong="G3778"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* taught \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \add Jewish\add* laws \w realized|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* accusing \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w when|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w told|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w parable|strong="G3850"\w* \add about what those wicked men did\add*. \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* immediately \w tried|strong="G2212"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w find|strong="G1097"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w way|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* seize [MTY] \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \add they did not seize him, because\add* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \add what\add* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w* \add there would do if they did that\add*.
